com.edugility.nomen.mvel

Class NameResolverFactory

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.mvel2.integration.impl.BaseVariableResolverFactory
      • com.edugility.nomen.mvel.NameResolverFactory
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Named, Serializable, org.mvel2.integration.VariableResolverFactory

    public class NameResolverFactory
extends org.mvel2.integration.impl.BaseVariableResolverFactory
implements Named
    A BaseVariableResolverFactory that produces NameResolver instances for use by MVEL expressions.

    Subclasses of this class normally have to override only the getName(NameType) method.

    Author:
    Laird Nelson
    See Also:
    NameResolver, MVEL, BaseVariableResolverFactory, VariableResolverFactory, VariableResolver, getName(NameType), Name.getValue(), NameValue.setAtomic(boolean), Serialized Form

      • getName

        public Name getName(NameType nameType)
        Given a NameType, returns a Name corresponding to it in some fashion.

        This method may return null.

        The default implementation of this method invokes the Named.getName(NameType) method on the value of the named field.

        Specified by:
        getName in interface Named
        Parameters:
        nameType - the NameType for which a corresponding Name should be returned; may be null
        Returns:
        a Name corresponding to the supplied NameType, or null
        See Also:

      • isResolveable

        public boolean isResolveable(String name)
        Returns true if name is equal to the value of a NameType that, when passed to Named.getName(NameType), results in a non-null Name, or if subsequent VariableResolvers are able to make sense of the supplied name parameter.
        Specified by:
        isResolveable in interface org.mvel2.integration.VariableResolverFactory
        Parameters:
        name - the value of a NameType; may be null
        Returns:
        true if this NameResolverFactory or any of its chained VariableResolverFactory instances can resolve an MVEL variable of the given name; false otherwise
        See Also:
        VariableResolverFactory, BaseVariableResolverFactory.isNextResolveable(String), VariableResolver, NameResolver
